        "title": "How to link javascript functions with applet?",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to make a form page in a java applet. Now after making textbox and submit button, how can I validate this text-box? Anyone if can tell me if I can link JS code to applet and if yes, then how? <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>package com.tcs.applet;\n\nimport java.awt.*;\nimport java.awt.event.*;\nimport java.applet.*;\n\nimport javax.swing.JButton;\n\npublic class MyApplet extends Applet  { \nTextField inputLine = new TextField(15);  \nprivate JButton button = new JButton(\"Submit\");\npublic MyApplet() {\n    add(inputLine);\n   add(button);\n}\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
